UML:Package.name: 1. Service providers or developers will upload AAL services

UML:TaggedValue.value:
Uploading of AAL services will be allowed for service providers and developers roles
  • Developers will be allowed to upload software directly from depot server or client (by using artifact's meta data & additional meta data from developer). In this case uStore will save link to the artifact from specific develop depot for future usage and can also save specific user/password for this (if it's not same as an uStore user).
  • Developers will provide software that was not developed using develop depot
  • Service providers will provide all kinds of services
  • Uploaded service will be associated with a group and/or users (as selected by user during uploading process)
1. Service providers or developers will upload AAL services
uStore will exploit dependency analysis and compatibility analysis to avoid that AAL Services are bought twice when, for example, other AAL Services exist

An approval process for ensuring that resources made available in the uStore are consistent with universAAL architectural policies will exist on the uStore web site
  • For software conformance tools will be implemented in task 3.3 and will be integrated in the uStore
For other services, uStore will save a policy that would be checked for every new proposed service

Software components (e.g OSGi Bundle, Android Package, .NET-based) on multiple execution environments (e.g Android, Windows, Symbian and Linux) will be supported
1. Service providers or developers will upload AAL services
AAL service will include software (applications and device drivers), hardware, courses and/or human resources or any combination of them or other AAL services

Capability-requirement model will be used: every service will provide its requirements and capabilities it provides in a similar way to the described in the following specifications:
  • JSR-124 http://jcp.org/aboutJava/communityprocess/final/jsr124/
  • OSGi Bundle repository http://www.osgi.org/download/rfc-0112_BundleRepository.pdf
  • There MAY be additional mechanisms to group few services together to answer user's request (more details needed here)
